Quantitative Strategy Performance Overview
1 Feb, 2002 - 14 Jan, 2025

Benchmark is EUREKA HEDGE FUND INDEX

This report compares the backtest performance of a long-short quantitative strategy with the Eureka Hedge Fund Index over the period from February 1, 2002, to January 14, 2025. The strategy uses solely S&P 500 components and uses financing rates derived from the Federal Reserve Rate plus a 0.5% spread.

The strategy employs a gross leverage of up to 10x. The strategy allows a scalable risk management that can be tailored to different levels of risk tolerance. By adjusting the leverage, the risk exposure can be fine-tuned to match specific investment goals, offering flexibility in risk control.

Importantly, the backtest addresses common issues in financial modeling, such as selection bias and overfitting, as highlighted in Marcos LÃ³pez de Prado's work, particularly in his book Advances in Financial Machine Learning. To mitigate these risks, the backtest was conducted using out-of-sample data and a rolling window approach. This methodology ensures that the results are not influenced by hindsight or lookahead bias, providing a more realistic and forward-looking evaluation of performance.
